{"PageNumber":15,"Angle":0,"RotatedAngle":0,"Height":2160,"Width":1620,"OriginHeight":0,"OriginWidth":0,"Elements":[{"Index":0,"Type":"header","Text":"Dependency Inversion Principle (DIP)","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":240,"Y":115},"LeftTop":{"X":240,"Y":50},"RightBottom":{"X":927,"Y":115},"RightTop":{"X":927,"Y":50}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":1,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"The Dependency Inversion Principle (DIP) is one of the SOLID principles of object-oriented design. It suggests that high-level modules should not depend on low-level modules, but both should depend on abstractions.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":99,"Y":340},"LeftTop":{"X":99,"Y":191},"RightBottom":{"X":1536,"Y":340},"RightTop":{"X":1536,"Y":191}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":2,"Type":"figure","Text":"","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":91,"Y":871},"LeftTop":{"X":91,"Y":363},"RightBottom":{"X":603,"Y":871},"RightTop":{"X":603,"Y":363}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":[{"Index":0,"Type":"figure_text","Text":"graph TD     A[Violation of principle] --> B[Calculator]     B --> C[Add]     C --> D[Subtract]","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":91,"Y":871},"LeftTop":{"X":91,"Y":363},"RightBottom":{"X":603,"Y":871},"RightTop":{"X":603,"Y":363}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":0,"group_type":""}],"ImagePath":"images/8407aa31ae118d7a42bad9470db85933-image.png","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":3,"Type":"figure","Text":"","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":793,"Y":871},"LeftTop":{"X":793,"Y":357},"RightBottom":{"X":1293,"Y":871},"RightTop":{"X":1293,"Y":357}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":[{"Index":0,"Type":"figure_text","Text":"graph TD     A[Compilant of principle] --> B[Calculator]     B --> C[Interface]     C --> D[Multiply]     C --> E[Subtract]","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":793,"Y":871},"LeftTop":{"X":793,"Y":357},"RightBottom":{"X":1293,"Y":871},"RightTop":{"X":1293,"Y":357}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":0,"group_type":""}],"ImagePath":"images/fe4cf6205e5cfe44a9fa5d012a481d0e-image.png","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":4,"Type":"title","Text":"#  Before DIP:","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":96,"Y":955},"LeftTop":{"X":96,"Y":912},"RightBottom":{"X":321,"Y":955},"RightTop":{"X":321,"Y":912}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":5,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"Suppose you have a simple scenario where you have a LightBulb class, and you want to create a Switch class that can control the bulb:","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":91,"Y":1063},"LeftTop":{"X":91,"Y":966},"RightBottom":{"X":1368,"Y":1063},"RightTop":{"X":1368,"Y":966}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":6,"Type":"code","Text":"```\nclass LightBulb {\n    public void turnOn() {\n        // Code to turn on the bulb\n    }\n    public void turnOff() {\n        // Code to turn off the bulb\n    }\n}\nclass Switch {\n    private LightBulb bulb;\n    public Switch(LightBulb bulb) {\n        this.bulb = bulb;\n    }\n    public void operate() {\n        // Code to operate the bulb (e.g., turn it on or off)\n        bulb.turnOn();\n    }\n}\n```","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":91,"Y":2068},"LeftTop":{"X":91,"Y":1117},"RightBottom":{"X":893,"Y":2068},"RightTop":{"X":893,"Y":1117}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""}]}